biography.text:
Once upon a time in a studio, Dubfire found himself in a surreal moment that felt like a dream—or perhaps a funky fairy tale. There he was, coaching the iconic Stevie Nicks through a fresh rendition of their hit "Dreams." As he recalls the two-day recording session, it’s clear that this was not just any collaboration; it was a magical intersection of worlds, leaving Dubfire pinching himself in disbelief.

Fast forward to today, and Deep Dish is back after a 30-year adventure through the musical landscape. Sharam insists their hiatus was less of a breakup and more like two old friends taking a scenic detour on a creative journey. They’ve always been in touch, and now they’re ready to reunite and reclaim their dance floor throne.

Their return is fueled by a shiny new deal with Armada Music, which has unleashed their classic anthems like “Flashdance” and “Say Hello” into the digital realm. It’s as if they’ve sprinkled a little pixie dust on their catalog, and fans are here for it. But it’s not just about revisiting the past; they’re blending old-school flair with fresh sounds, crafting tunes that defy traditional genres. No more boxes or labels—just pure musical exploration!

So, music lovers, buckle up! The reunion of Deep Dish isn’t just a nostalgic return; it’s a delightful rediscovery of what it means to groove through time, proving that the dance floor remains their true playground. Get ready to dance—because this is just the beginning of their enchanting new chapter!
